<p></p><div id="attachment_223109" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="max-width: 210px;"><img class="wp-image-223109 size-medium" src="https://cdn.ps.emap.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/Ken-Fero-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300"><p class="wp-caption-text">Ken Fero</p></div>
<p>“This research is not only focused on collecting stories of racial discrimination and the impact of long-term discrimination on individual and institutional approaches to a crisis.</p>
<p>“Viewing the ‘pandemic as a portal’ through which we can re-shape our direction as a society, we will centre the insights of those on the frontline as a crucial asset in creating significant change.”</p>
<p>The study had been awarded funding from the Arts and Humanities Research Council, following a call from the UK Research and Innovation (UKRI) government department for projects to explore the impact of the pandemic.</p>
<p>Those behind the project are appealing to individuals who would like to be involved in the study to contact the team at nursingnarrativesuk@gmail.com.</p>
